WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:19.169
- What did you get?
- Building plans.

3
00:00:19.170 --> 00:00:21.749
Sentinel Services
Headquarters. the Capitol.

4
00:00:21.750 --> 00:00:24.719
Of course. The plan is to
wipe out the entire government?

5
00:00:24.720 --> 00:00:26.450
This attack is coming.

6
00:00:28.020 --> 00:00:31.059
You people took everything
from me! Never again.

7
00:00:31.060 --> 00:00:33.699
- [GUN COCKS]
- [GRUNTS]

8
00:00:33.700 --> 00:00:34.980
Clarice. come on.

9
00:00:37.100 --> 00:00:39.330
No!

10
00:00:42.270 --> 00:00:43.600
This is your fault.

11
00:00:43.610 --> 00:00:45.009
She shouldn't have been down there.

12
00:00:45.010 --> 00:00:47.070
I gave her a place where she belonged.

13
00:00:47.080 --> 00:00:49.479
- Blink was...
- Stop calling her Blink!

14
00:00:49.480 --> 00:00:51.850
- It's the name she chose!
- [GRUNTS]

15
00:00:53.180 --> 00:00:54.710
REED [ON PHONE]: You need to come home.

16
00:00:54.720 --> 00:00:55.949
I don't think I can do that.

17
00:00:55.950 --> 00:00:57.260
When I attacked that Purifier.

18
00:00:57.270 --> 00:00:58.299
you were afraid of me.

19
00:00:58.300 --> 00:01:00.029
I belong here. I am a monster.

20
00:01:00.030 --> 00:01:01.519
REED: <i>Today I killed a man.</i>

21
00:01:01.520 --> 00:01:02.520
<i>If you're a monster.</i>

22
00:01:02.521 --> 00:01:03.650
son. then so am I.

23
00:01:04.820 --> 00:01:07.310
<i>We're your family. you belong with us.</i>

24
00:01:13.860 --> 00:01:15.559
PHOEBE: Andy and Lorna are gone.

25
00:01:15.560 --> 00:01:17.370
We could sense Lorna's
uncertainty. but...

26
00:01:17.380 --> 00:01:19.880
Someone thought they had a special bond.

27
00:01:19.930 --> 00:01:22.370
Such a shame we have to kill them.

28
00:01:22.430 --> 00:01:24.729
NEWSWOMAN [ON TV]:
People are still reacting

29
00:01:24.730 --> 00:01:28.029
to the utter devastation
of the first mass casualty

30
00:01:28.030 --> 00:01:30.129
mutant attack on American soil.

31
00:01:30.130 --> 00:01:32.339
MAN: There was. like.
these flashes in the sky.

32
00:01:32.340 --> 00:01:34.240
a-a-and then there
was bodies everywhere.

33
00:01:34.250 --> 00:01:35.579
I've never seen anything like it.

34
00:01:35.580 --> 00:01:37.659
NEWSMAN: First responders across Dallas

35
00:01:37.660 --> 00:01:39.309
are doing everything they can.

36
00:01:39.310 --> 00:01:40.659
but it's now becoming clear

37
00:01:40.660 --> 00:01:42.809
the death toll will be in the thousands.

38
00:01:42.810 --> 00:01:45.089
Mom. is that gonna happen here?

39
00:01:45.090 --> 00:01:47.649
No. sweetie. It's gonna be okay.

40
00:01:47.650 --> 00:01:48.950
Hey!

41
00:01:49.780 --> 00:01:52.149
- Dad!
- Andy. come here.

42
00:01:52.150 --> 00:01:53.570
Oh. it's good to see you.

43
00:01:53.580 --> 00:01:54.599
Yeah.

44
00:01:54.600 --> 00:01:56.539
Sorry it took so long.
The roads were jammed.

45
00:01:56.540 --> 00:01:58.109
You didn't have to come home.

46
00:01:58.110 --> 00:01:59.219
Of course I did.

47
00:01:59.220 --> 00:02:00.589
Most of the others were
out the door as soon

48
00:02:00.590 --> 00:02:02.049
as the first news reports came in.

49
00:02:02.050 --> 00:02:04.599
They've closed down some of the
government buildings. just in case.

50
00:02:04.600 --> 00:02:06.850
- Hi. Lauren. how are you?
- I'm scared.

51
00:02:09.720 --> 00:02:12.589
It just feels like a bad dream.

52
00:02:12.590 --> 00:02:14.790
NEWSMAN 2: ...more attacks
could be on the way.

53
00:02:21.140 --> 00:02:23.270
♪ ♪

54
00:02:29.730 --> 00:02:31.290
NEWSWOMAN: The incident in Dallas marks

55
00:02:31.300 --> 00:02:33.579
the deadliest mutant
attack in American history.

56
00:02:33.580 --> 00:02:34.979
[TV TURNS OFF]

57
00:02:34.980 --> 00:02:37.619
CAITLIN: I think that's
enough news for today.

58
00:02:37.620 --> 00:02:40.890
Kids are asleep. Finally.

59
00:02:44.290 --> 00:02:48.159
I wanted to tell them that
we'll keep them safe. that...

60
00:02:48.160 --> 00:02:50.629
that this could never happen to them.

61
00:02:50.630 --> 00:02:54.730
but how do you make that promise?

62
00:03:00.380 --> 00:03:02.279
You know. we talked
about me transferring

63
00:03:02.280 --> 00:03:04.310
to the Mutant Crimes Division.

64
00:03:05.810 --> 00:03:08.649
You really want to do that now?

65
00:03:08.650 --> 00:03:12.189
I just feel like maybe this
is telling us something.

66
00:03:12.190 --> 00:03:15.030
This is the fight of our time. Cait.

67
00:03:16.660 --> 00:03:18.789
I can't just sit by on the sidelines.

68
00:03:18.790 --> 00:03:22.430
It's the only way I can think
of to keep our kids safe.

69
00:03:25.370 --> 00:03:28.599
I can't say I'm excited
about you jumping

70
00:03:28.600 --> 00:03:31.000
into the middle of what happened today.

71
00:03:31.010 --> 00:03:35.540
but if you feel like you
need to do that. I get it.

72
00:03:39.930 --> 00:03:45.050
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

73
00:03:47.490 --> 00:03:50.310
POLARIS: <i>We have to move
against Reeva now.</i>

74
00:03:50.320 --> 00:03:53.359
In the next 24 hours. she plans
on taking out Sentinel Services

75
00:03:53.360 --> 00:03:55.329
and then the whole dang government.

76
00:03:55.330 --> 00:03:57.699
Thousands of innocent
people will be dead.

77
00:03:57.700 --> 00:03:59.369
So we're just gonna attack?

78
00:03:59.370 --> 00:04:01.449
Last I heard. she was in a fortress.

79
00:04:01.450 --> 00:04:04.569
Well. we didn't have the power
to attack a fortress before.

80
00:04:04.570 --> 00:04:05.920
Now we do.

81
00:04:05.930 --> 00:04:07.760
If they can take down the
Inner Circle headquarters...

82
00:04:07.770 --> 00:04:11.340
Wait. You want Andy and
Lauren to destroy a high-rise?

83
00:04:11.350 --> 00:04:14.009
CAITLIN: God knows I am all for
bringing down the Inner Circle.

84
00:04:14.010 --> 00:04:15.419
but there has to be another way

85
00:04:15.420 --> 00:04:17.470
that doesn't involve
Andy and Lauren destroying

86
00:04:17.480 --> 00:04:18.919
an entire building.

87
00:04:18.920 --> 00:04:21.050
THUNDERBIRD: There is no other way.

88
00:04:21.060 --> 00:04:24.020
If we do this. we don't
lose anyone else here.

89
00:04:24.030 --> 00:04:26.359
POLARIS: It's true. But
we can't afford to wait.

90
00:04:26.360 --> 00:04:28.699
- It's too much.
- It's all right.

91
00:04:28.700 --> 00:04:30.660
I think we can do it.

92
00:04:30.670 --> 00:04:31.810
Are you sure?

93
00:04:31.820 --> 00:04:33.249
LAUREN: In a way. I feel like

94
00:04:33.250 --> 00:04:35.399
we've been preparing
for this for a long time.

95
00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:37.239
We can stop Reeva.

96
00:04:37.240 --> 00:04:40.040
We have this power. we might as
well use it for something good.

97
00:04:48.050 --> 00:04:49.379
ESME: It's what we thought.

98
00:04:49.380 --> 00:04:51.619
Lorna and Andrew went back
to the Mutant Underground.

99
00:04:51.620 --> 00:04:54.350
Pathetic. really. I guess
greatness skips a generation.

100
00:04:54.360 --> 00:04:55.759
Or three.

101
00:04:55.760 --> 00:04:57.020
See? I told you.

102
00:04:57.030 --> 00:04:58.940
I knew that Lorna bitch got Max killed.

103
00:04:58.950 --> 00:05:03.059
- What the hell do we do now?
- We move forward with the plan.

104
00:05:03.060 --> 00:05:06.190
Yes. their loss is a setback.
but they can be replaced.

105
00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:07.999
Lorna was going to block communications

106
00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:09.429
using her abilities.

107
00:05:09.430 --> 00:05:11.019
No. it isn't as elegant.

108
00:05:11.020 --> 00:05:13.939
but the same can be
done using explosives.

109
00:05:13.940 --> 00:05:15.939
What about taking
down Sentinel Services?

110
00:05:15.940 --> 00:05:17.570
The whole idea was to have Andy do it.

111
00:05:17.580 --> 00:05:19.709
Yes. that part of the plan
will have to change as well.

112
00:05:19.710 --> 00:05:22.649
but it will go forward.

113
00:05:22.650 --> 00:05:24.949
Now. if you'll excuse me.

114
00:05:24.950 --> 00:05:26.790
I have to make some arrangements.

115
00:05:31.460 --> 00:05:33.460
[DIALING]

116
00:05:35.600 --> 00:05:37.499
- [LINE RINGING]
- RYAN [ON PHONE]: Hello?

117
00:05:37.500 --> 00:05:40.230
Mr. Ryan. Rise and shine.

118
00:05:40.240 --> 00:05:41.899
RYAN: Do you know what time it is?

119
00:05:41.900 --> 00:05:43.569
It's time for you to get to work.

120
00:05:43.570 --> 00:05:45.339
RYAN: What is it now?

121
00:05:45.340 --> 00:05:48.340
I have a job for your Purifier friends.

122
00:06:02.020 --> 00:06:04.120
ANDY: Dad?

123
00:06:04.130 --> 00:06:05.989
You feeling okay?

124
00:06:05.990 --> 00:06:08.129
Yeah. I'm good.

125
00:06:08.130 --> 00:06:09.630
Sorry.

126
00:06:12.330 --> 00:06:14.430
You ready?

127
00:06:14.440 --> 00:06:16.499
Yeah. We're supposed
to be getting our stuff.

128
00:06:16.500 --> 00:06:19.370
but I don't have any stuff. so...

129
00:06:22.680 --> 00:06:24.720
I thought you were taking medicine.

130
00:06:26.980 --> 00:06:28.649
I stopped.

131
00:06:28.650 --> 00:06:30.180
Why?

132
00:06:30.190 --> 00:06:34.319
I felt like I had to
face this thing head-on.

133
00:06:34.320 --> 00:06:37.020
For so long. I've been trying
to make sense of it all.

134
00:06:37.030 --> 00:06:39.060
Yeah.

135
00:06:40.500 --> 00:06:42.300
Me. too.

136
00:06:49.200 --> 00:06:53.639
After I left. I wanted to
come home so many times.

137
00:06:53.640 --> 00:06:56.409
I just thought that I was in so deep.

138
00:06:56.410 --> 00:06:58.579
But...

139
00:06:58.580 --> 00:07:00.879
after what you said last night.

140
00:07:00.880 --> 00:07:03.549
I...

141
00:07:03.550 --> 00:07:06.249
I just felt like I was
part of the family again.

142
00:07:06.250 --> 00:07:07.490
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

143
00:07:10.690 --> 00:07:14.429
When you were away. it was like
a part of me had been torn away.

144
00:07:14.430 --> 00:07:17.519
like I was never gonna be whole again.

145
00:07:17.520 --> 00:07:20.099
You are always my son.

146
00:07:20.100 --> 00:07:22.400
Nothing could ever change that.

147
00:07:25.940 --> 00:07:28.009
A lot of these files are on stations

148
00:07:28.010 --> 00:07:30.709
that don't exist anymore.

149
00:07:30.710 --> 00:07:32.199
People that are gone.

150
00:07:32.200 --> 00:07:34.089
THUNDERBIRD: Marcos. there's
nothing left to rebuild.

151
00:07:34.090 --> 00:07:37.550
Just... just burn it all.

152
00:07:39.490 --> 00:07:41.389
All of this is my fault.

153
00:07:41.390 --> 00:07:43.439
Lorna.

154
00:07:43.440 --> 00:07:45.659
It is.

155
00:07:45.660 --> 00:07:48.290
I was fighting for a dream.

156
00:07:48.300 --> 00:07:51.460
A dream of a place for all of us.

157
00:07:51.470 --> 00:07:53.399
I believed in Reeva's lie.

158
00:07:53.400 --> 00:07:55.530
And Clarice died because of it.

159
00:08:08.550 --> 00:08:12.480
Marcos told me you saw her at the end.

160
00:08:12.490 --> 00:08:16.359
Yeah. Uh...

161
00:08:16.360 --> 00:08:19.089
Jace Turner shot her.

162
00:08:19.090 --> 00:08:21.829
She was making a portal.

163
00:08:21.830 --> 00:08:24.660
I could still feel her. but...

164
00:08:24.670 --> 00:08:26.830
she was just gone.

165
00:08:36.080 --> 00:08:39.910
Look. I'm... I'm sorry.

166
00:08:42.120 --> 00:08:45.520
You just promise me
that you're gonna fight.

167
00:08:48.060 --> 00:08:49.720
I promise.

168
00:08:50.930 --> 00:08:53.169
ECLIPSE: That's it.

169
00:08:53.170 --> 00:08:54.529
That's the last of it.

170
00:08:54.530 --> 00:08:55.999
We should. uh.

171
00:08:56.000 --> 00:08:58.260
we should get the
Struckers and head out.

172
00:08:58.270 --> 00:09:00.300
John. what?

173
00:09:02.570 --> 00:09:05.070
There's a lot of trucks
coming down the street.

174
00:09:06.840 --> 00:09:09.480
[MEN SHOUTING]

175
00:09:10.550 --> 00:09:11.840
Purifiers.

176
00:09:19.280 --> 00:09:20.950
We're at the Westke Apartments.

177
00:09:20.960 --> 00:09:23.669
We have the building
surrounded. Proudstar's in there?

178
00:09:23.670 --> 00:09:26.970
Not just him. All your friends
from the Mutant Underground.

179
00:09:26.980 --> 00:09:28.679
The real question is whether

180
00:09:28.680 --> 00:09:30.249
you're gonna let them escape again.

181
00:09:30.250 --> 00:09:31.479
JACE: We got every exit covered.

182
00:09:31.480 --> 00:09:33.819
We got overlapping fields
of fire in every direction.

183
00:09:33.820 --> 00:09:35.310
Just make sure nobody gets in our way.

184
00:09:35.320 --> 00:09:36.379
RYAN: The local police

185
00:09:36.380 --> 00:09:38.719
are very upset about Officer
Wilson's death yesterday.

186
00:09:38.720 --> 00:09:39.960
They'll look the other way.

187
00:09:40.010 --> 00:09:41.740
If you want justice for your family.

188
00:09:41.750 --> 00:09:43.519
now is the time.

189
00:09:43.520 --> 00:09:45.279
JACE: I've been waiting
a long time for this.

190
00:09:45.280 --> 00:09:47.850
I won't let you down.

191
00:09:49.470 --> 00:09:51.480
[DOOR OPENING]

192
00:09:51.490 --> 00:09:53.559
I just checked the back.
They've got that covered.

193
00:09:53.560 --> 00:09:55.759
and the roads are blocked. the
Purifier line is three deep.

194
00:09:55.760 --> 00:09:57.570
If we take one step
out there. we're dead.

195
00:09:57.620 --> 00:09:59.389
We should've known she'd
call Ryan to take us out.

196
00:09:59.390 --> 00:10:00.770
She's not taking any chances.

197
00:10:00.780 --> 00:10:03.440
This is not just
rednecks in pickup trucks.

198
00:10:03.450 --> 00:10:05.329
They've got body armor. bigger guns.

199
00:10:05.330 --> 00:10:07.569
They're spread out all over.
some of them are out of reach.

200
00:10:07.570 --> 00:10:09.509
And they got us covered
from every angle.

201
00:10:09.510 --> 00:10:11.970
POLARIS: It looks like
Reeva took this personally.

202
00:10:13.210 --> 00:10:15.640
She's not the only one
who took things personally.

203
00:10:16.530 --> 00:10:18.639
- My husband is in there.
- I understand that. ma'am.

204
00:10:18.640 --> 00:10:19.819
We'll get him out.

205
00:10:19.820 --> 00:10:21.749
We're gonna protect all the humans.

206
00:10:21.750 --> 00:10:24.049
We'll get him out. okay? Trust me.

207
00:10:24.050 --> 00:10:26.419
PURIFIER 1: We should just go in. man.

208
00:10:26.420 --> 00:10:27.719
There's families up there.

209
00:10:27.720 --> 00:10:30.350
We had Proudstar at the
compound with 50 men.

210
00:10:30.360 --> 00:10:32.220
How many of them died that day?

211
00:10:32.230 --> 00:10:36.110
No. They know they can't
stay in there forever.

212
00:10:36.120 --> 00:10:37.479
They're gonna have to make a move soon.

213
00:10:37.480 --> 00:10:39.470
and when they do. we cut them down.

214
00:10:41.170 --> 00:10:43.770
We do this right. the Mutant
Underground ends today.

215
00:10:45.940 --> 00:10:47.409
God. there's so many of them.

216
00:10:47.410 --> 00:10:48.999
REED: They're setting up a perimeter.

217
00:10:49.000 --> 00:10:50.730
Looks like they're
planning to wait us out.

218
00:10:50.740 --> 00:10:52.359
CAITLIN: I don't want
to take any chances.

219
00:10:52.360 --> 00:10:54.760
I've got some guns in the
storage room downstairs.

220
00:10:54.770 --> 00:10:55.849
REED: You do?

221
00:10:55.850 --> 00:10:57.049
You didn't tell me that.

222
00:10:57.050 --> 00:10:59.219
I'm telling you now.

223
00:10:59.220 --> 00:11:01.420
Stay put. we'll be right back.

224
00:11:15.870 --> 00:11:17.370
Here you go.

225
00:11:19.630 --> 00:11:21.109
Where'd you get all these guns?

226
00:11:21.110 --> 00:11:22.679
It's America. Reed.

227
00:11:22.680 --> 00:11:24.040
Stores sell them.

228
00:11:26.050 --> 00:11:28.779
Look. I don't have an X-Gene.

229
00:11:28.780 --> 00:11:30.980
I figured it was the next best thing.

230
00:11:32.890 --> 00:11:34.249
Hey.

231
00:11:34.250 --> 00:11:36.289
Is the pain bad?

232
00:11:36.290 --> 00:11:38.720
No. It's just. um...

233
00:11:38.730 --> 00:11:40.489
frustrating.

234
00:11:40.490 --> 00:11:43.829
All I ever wanted to do
was protect my children.

235
00:11:43.830 --> 00:11:46.970
I have this ability. and there
is nothing I can do with it.

236
00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:49.599
Just breathe. okay?

237
00:11:49.600 --> 00:11:50.739
Yeah.

238
00:11:50.740 --> 00:11:52.469
We're gonna get through this.

239
00:11:52.470 --> 00:11:54.670
- [TAKES DEEP BREATH]
- Yeah.

240
00:12:05.120 --> 00:12:07.289
[SIGHS]

241
00:12:07.290 --> 00:12:08.849
You still working?

242
00:12:08.850 --> 00:12:10.880
Yeah. just some briefs for Monday.

243
00:12:15.030 --> 00:12:17.159
Want to take a break?

244
00:12:17.160 --> 00:12:18.360
I. uh...

245
00:12:18.370 --> 00:12:19.860
The kids are out.

246
00:12:19.870 --> 00:12:21.969
Your mission to save the world

247
00:12:21.970 --> 00:12:24.760
from mutant crime can wait an hour.

248
00:12:24.770 --> 00:12:27.439
Yeah. I guess an hour won't hurt.

249
00:12:27.440 --> 00:12:30.379
Yeah. I-I think this particular hour

250
00:12:30.380 --> 00:12:33.640
might even help. [CHUCKLES]

251
00:12:33.650 --> 00:12:35.110
[PHONE VIBRATES]

252
00:12:37.150 --> 00:12:38.720
- [SIGHS]
- Work?

253
00:12:40.650 --> 00:12:42.019
No. it's...

254
00:12:42.020 --> 00:12:43.629
it's Lauren.

255
00:12:43.630 --> 00:12:45.689
Hang on. Hey.

256
00:12:45.690 --> 00:12:47.289
[CRYING]: Hi. I need you.

257
00:12:47.290 --> 00:12:48.829
Can you please come get me?

258
00:12:48.830 --> 00:12:50.809
Wait. S-Slow down. I thought you were

259
00:12:50.810 --> 00:12:52.109
at Emma's party. What...

260
00:12:52.110 --> 00:12:53.560
Yeah. I am.

261
00:12:53.570 --> 00:12:55.700
Something happened to me. Dad.

262
00:12:56.740 --> 00:12:58.869
There was a mutant attack.

263
00:12:58.870 --> 00:13:01.030
- I'm outside.
- Are you hurt?

264
00:13:01.040 --> 00:13:02.209
No. no. I'm fine.

265
00:13:02.210 --> 00:13:04.069
Just please come get me. Please?

266
00:13:04.070 --> 00:13:05.809
- What happened?
- There's been a mutant attack

267
00:13:05.810 --> 00:13:07.179
at the party. I'm gonna go get her.

268
00:13:07.180 --> 00:13:08.340
I'll be right there. honey.

269
00:13:11.520 --> 00:13:13.889
If it comes down to it. we
might have to use Fenris.

270
00:13:13.890 --> 00:13:15.320
take them all out.

271
00:13:16.690 --> 00:13:19.420
I don't want to think
about that right now.

272
00:13:19.430 --> 00:13:20.919
[EXHALES] You really want to kill

273
00:13:20.920 --> 00:13:23.949
- all those people?
- I don't like hurting people.

274
00:13:23.950 --> 00:13:25.980
I know you think I do.

275
00:13:25.990 --> 00:13:28.199
All that stuff that
happened at the Inner Circle.

276
00:13:28.200 --> 00:13:29.669
everything we did.

277
00:13:29.670 --> 00:13:31.439
even the worst stuff...

278
00:13:31.440 --> 00:13:33.840
I did it because I
wanted to help people.

279
00:13:36.840 --> 00:13:38.740
[CREAKING NEARBY]

280
00:13:38.750 --> 00:13:41.009
ANDY: What?

281
00:13:41.010 --> 00:13:42.850
The door.

282
00:13:43.880 --> 00:13:46.049
Mom closed it.

283
00:13:46.050 --> 00:13:47.250
Yeah. what the hell?

284
00:13:53.760 --> 00:13:55.390
- [GASPS]
- Surprise.

285
00:13:56.730 --> 00:13:57.900
[GASPS]

286
00:14:00.300 --> 00:14:03.099
FROST SISTERS: On your knees.

287
00:14:03.100 --> 00:14:05.700
- Don't fight.
- [YELPS]

288
00:14:05.710 --> 00:14:07.069
[GRUNTS]

289
00:14:07.070 --> 00:14:10.039
Andrew. Lauren.

290
00:14:10.040 --> 00:14:11.940
Is that any way to treat guests?

291
00:14:13.910 --> 00:14:15.710
- You're doing great.
- [PANTING]

292
00:14:15.720 --> 00:14:18.930
[CHUCKLES] Remember that
couples meditation class

293
00:14:18.940 --> 00:14:21.219
we took in Cancún
before Lauren was born?

294
00:14:21.220 --> 00:14:23.989
Yeah. I don't remember them
covering this situation. though.

295
00:14:23.990 --> 00:14:27.159
I told you we should've
taken the two-hour class.

296
00:14:27.160 --> 00:14:28.830
Next time.

297
00:14:32.900 --> 00:14:34.129
Andy?

298
00:14:34.130 --> 00:14:35.970
Lauren!

299
00:14:45.280 --> 00:14:46.639
It's done.

300
00:14:46.640 --> 00:14:48.929
- REEVA: Everything go smoothly?
- Smoothly?

301
00:14:48.930 --> 00:14:51.399
Fade almost got us killed
sneaking past the Purifiers.

302
00:14:51.400 --> 00:14:53.969
I don't need the details.
Did you get what you came for?

303
00:14:53.970 --> 00:14:56.669
Yes. They're here. Reeva.

304
00:14:56.670 --> 00:14:59.169
I'm worried... making them
use their powers like this.

305
00:14:59.170 --> 00:15:00.739
they could snap. they
could have a stroke.

306
00:15:00.740 --> 00:15:02.139
As long as the job is done.

307
00:15:02.140 --> 00:15:04.969
Next time you call.
you better have results.

308
00:15:04.970 --> 00:15:07.330
RYAN [ON TV]: ...hide
behind political correctness.

309
00:15:07.340 --> 00:15:10.980
The time has come to demand
that our elected leaders

310
00:15:10.990 --> 00:15:14.029
stop the talk and <i>do</i> something.

311
00:15:14.030 --> 00:15:15.819
We're whistling in the dark. people.

312
00:15:15.820 --> 00:15:17.820
There's going to be a mutant attack.

313
00:15:17.830 --> 00:15:20.659
When it comes. is
America going to be ready?

314
00:15:20.660 --> 00:15:23.130
- Not at all.
- It's time to pick up...

315
00:15:24.780 --> 00:15:27.140
Is there anything? Do you see them?

316
00:15:32.870 --> 00:15:34.090
[EXHALES]

317
00:15:38.330 --> 00:15:41.060
Still having trouble tracking.
Keep seeing Clarice everywhere.

318
00:15:41.070 --> 00:15:42.210
I'm trying. but...

319
00:15:49.340 --> 00:15:51.010
Frost sisters were here.

320
00:15:51.060 --> 00:15:52.789
ECLIPSE: The Purifiers have
this building surrounded.

321
00:15:52.790 --> 00:15:53.859
How did it happen?

322
00:15:53.860 --> 00:15:56.469
- Fade.
- God. I hate that guy.

323
00:15:56.470 --> 00:15:58.060
Reeva's plan depends on destroying

324
00:15:58.070 --> 00:15:59.469
Sentinel Service Headquarters.

325
00:15:59.470 --> 00:16:01.399
If she's got Andy and Lauren...

326
00:16:01.400 --> 00:16:03.729
- We have to get to them.
- ECLIPSE: I'm all for it.

327
00:16:03.730 --> 00:16:05.639
How do we get out of here?

328
00:16:05.640 --> 00:16:07.809
I can move cars at the
roadblock. stop the bullets.

329
00:16:07.810 --> 00:16:10.659
Not from every single direction.
They've got every angle covered.

330
00:16:10.660 --> 00:16:12.810
REED: He's right. It's
like a wall out there.

331
00:16:12.820 --> 00:16:14.810
- There's no way through it.
- You need a way through?

332
00:16:14.820 --> 00:16:16.580
I can make one.

333
00:16:16.590 --> 00:16:19.549
- John. that is insane.
- It can work.

334
00:16:19.550 --> 00:16:21.539
REED: They've got the
entire street wired tight.

335
00:16:21.540 --> 00:16:22.799
THUNDERBIRD: Jace Turner wants

336
00:16:22.800 --> 00:16:24.520
the Mutant Underground.
but after what happened

337
00:16:24.530 --> 00:16:25.729
at the Purifier compound.

338
00:16:25.730 --> 00:16:27.929
he wants me. If I go out there.

339
00:16:27.930 --> 00:16:29.359
he's gonna throw
everything he can at me.

340
00:16:29.360 --> 00:16:31.160
That might be just
enough time for you guys

341
00:16:31.170 --> 00:16:32.729
- to drive out of here.
- CAITLIN: John. no. John.

342
00:16:32.730 --> 00:16:34.330
your body can take a lot of damage.

343
00:16:34.340 --> 00:16:35.830
but you are hardly bulletproof.

344
00:16:35.840 --> 00:16:37.239
You nearly died at that compound.

345
00:16:37.240 --> 00:16:39.319
Caitlin. I just need to last long enough

346
00:16:39.320 --> 00:16:41.370
to get them away from the gate.

347
00:16:43.440 --> 00:16:45.470
Look. John. I... I could help.

348
00:16:45.480 --> 00:16:46.949
- We could all...
- No. we can't risk it.

349
00:16:46.950 --> 00:16:48.690
The four of you have to
get to Lauren and Andy.

350
00:16:48.700 --> 00:16:50.499
- You have to stop Reeva.
- ECLIPSE: Brother.

351
00:16:50.500 --> 00:16:52.889
do you know what they
are going to do to you?

352
00:16:52.890 --> 00:16:54.790
Jace Turner took Clarice from me.

353
00:16:56.860 --> 00:16:59.030
He can't do anything worse.

354
00:17:03.300 --> 00:17:05.369
[EXHALES]

355
00:17:05.370 --> 00:17:07.570
♪ ♪

356
00:17:31.930 --> 00:17:34.130
♪ ♪

357
00:17:41.340 --> 00:17:43.470
[EXHALES FORCEFULLY]

358
00:17:46.110 --> 00:17:48.110
♪ ♪

359
00:17:56.080 --> 00:17:57.819
It's him! Fire!

360
00:17:57.820 --> 00:17:59.950
- [GUNFIRE]
- [GRUNTS]

361
00:18:14.160 --> 00:18:17.339
[GRUNTING]

362
00:18:17.340 --> 00:18:19.980
JACE: What are you
waiting for? Shoot him!

363
00:18:28.320 --> 00:18:29.650
[GRUNTS]

364
00:18:32.220 --> 00:18:33.820
[YELLS]

365
00:18:43.400 --> 00:18:46.030
[GRUNTING. CHOKING]

366
00:18:52.740 --> 00:18:54.510
[GUNFIRE RESUMES]

367
00:18:57.080 --> 00:18:58.380
[GRUNTS]

368
00:19:01.650 --> 00:19:03.080
[GROANS]

369
00:19:05.750 --> 00:19:07.250
[YELLS]

370
00:19:10.490 --> 00:19:11.820
[TIRES SQUEALING]

371
00:19:13.010 --> 00:19:15.560
The SUV! On the SUV!

372
00:19:23.870 --> 00:19:25.700
Go find him!

373
00:19:27.980 --> 00:19:30.989
♪ ♪

374
00:19:30.990 --> 00:19:32.959
Hey...

375
00:19:32.960 --> 00:19:34.599
- no cops yet.
- ECLIPSE: Let's hope

376
00:19:34.600 --> 00:19:36.850
our luck holds out till we
get to Sentinel Services.

377
00:19:36.860 --> 00:19:39.399
They're using the Morlock
tunnels to get around the city.

378
00:19:39.400 --> 00:19:41.800
There are some steam
grates at Elm and 15th.

379
00:19:41.810 --> 00:19:43.569
CAITLIN: Okay. I'll head that way.

380
00:19:43.570 --> 00:19:45.810
[QUIETLY]: Are you all right?

381
00:19:47.180 --> 00:19:48.879
I just can't stop it.

382
00:19:48.880 --> 00:19:50.310
It's okay.

383
00:19:50.320 --> 00:19:52.310
We made it out.

384
00:19:55.150 --> 00:19:58.589
REED: <i>You don't have
to be scared of mutants.</i>

385
00:19:58.590 --> 00:20:00.619
I'll protect you.

386
00:20:00.620 --> 00:20:04.329
This is the kind of thing
that makes you stronger.

387
00:20:04.330 --> 00:20:05.690
What do you mean?

388
00:20:07.630 --> 00:20:09.609
You remember... [TAKES DEEP BREATH]

389
00:20:09.610 --> 00:20:11.310
do you remember 7/15?

390
00:20:12.970 --> 00:20:15.440
How scary that day was?

391
00:20:17.140 --> 00:20:20.170
Watching the news on the TV all day...

392
00:20:20.180 --> 00:20:23.440
Thinking: Why?

393
00:20:23.450 --> 00:20:26.310
Something clicked for me that day.

394
00:20:26.320 --> 00:20:28.319
I knew that somehow...

395
00:20:28.320 --> 00:20:30.819
I had to be a part of it. that...

396
00:20:30.820 --> 00:20:33.619
that I could make a difference.

397
00:20:33.620 --> 00:20:35.789
That I<i> needed</i> to.

398
00:20:35.790 --> 00:20:38.160
And I think that's our job.

399
00:20:39.630 --> 00:20:41.899
When terrible things happen...

400
00:20:41.900 --> 00:20:46.530
like 7/15 and like what
happened to you tonight...

401
00:20:46.540 --> 00:20:49.970
we have to figure out what it means...

402
00:20:51.640 --> 00:20:54.210
...and how it can make us better.

403
00:20:57.250 --> 00:20:59.580
Dad?

404
00:21:02.890 --> 00:21:05.850
I need to tell you something.

405
00:21:05.860 --> 00:21:07.220
Okay.

406
00:21:11.490 --> 00:21:14.099
What is it?

407
00:21:14.100 --> 00:21:16.100
♪ ♪

408
00:21:17.600 --> 00:21:19.769
I'll always protect you.

409
00:21:19.770 --> 00:21:21.900
I promise.

410
00:21:23.840 --> 00:21:25.359
FROST SISTERS: <i>We're almost there.</i>

411
00:21:25.360 --> 00:21:26.910
It's just around the corner.

412
00:21:28.200 --> 00:21:29.669
- LAUREN: No.
- ANDY: Please.

413
00:21:29.670 --> 00:21:32.190
Still resisting. I suggest you behave.

414
00:21:32.200 --> 00:21:33.569
Or we'll make you behave.

415
00:21:33.570 --> 00:21:36.180
<i>- Stop resisting.</i>
- [GROANS]

416
00:21:36.240 --> 00:21:37.940
<i>Stop resisting.</i>

417
00:21:40.030 --> 00:21:42.430
What do you want from us?

418
00:21:42.440 --> 00:21:44.789
We just need some help
destroying a building.

419
00:21:44.790 --> 00:21:47.129
Please. don't make us
force you. It'll go easier

420
00:21:47.130 --> 00:21:48.699
- if you cooperate.
- But if you'd rather do it

421
00:21:48.700 --> 00:21:50.540
the hard way. that'll work. too.

422
00:21:51.910 --> 00:21:53.969
You left our parents to
be killed by Purifiers.

423
00:21:53.970 --> 00:21:56.139
The Purifiers will get
what's coming to them.

424
00:21:56.140 --> 00:21:58.099
I thought the whole point

425
00:21:58.100 --> 00:22:00.209
of doing this was to help mutants.

426
00:22:00.210 --> 00:22:02.740
This is mutant freedom? Forcing us...

427
00:22:02.750 --> 00:22:04.269
SOPHIE: We don't see it as forcing.

428
00:22:04.270 --> 00:22:06.819
Sometimes. people just need a
little help seeing the light.

429
00:22:06.820 --> 00:22:08.949
So we show it to them.

430
00:22:08.950 --> 00:22:11.389
[BOTH GROANING]

431
00:22:11.390 --> 00:22:13.250
- Wait.
- What is it?

432
00:22:13.260 --> 00:22:15.580
You know what happens if we
keep pushing them like this.

433
00:22:15.680 --> 00:22:17.089
We let you try to reason with them.

434
00:22:17.090 --> 00:22:18.419
They made their choice.

435
00:22:18.420 --> 00:22:20.359
W-We'll break them.
They might never recover.

436
00:22:20.360 --> 00:22:22.919
It's not like Reeva's gonna let
them live after what they did.

437
00:22:22.920 --> 00:22:25.100
SOPHIE: They might as well be useful.

438
00:22:25.110 --> 00:22:28.119
Now. let's get this over with.

439
00:22:28.120 --> 00:22:30.840
- PHOEBE/SOPHIE: Get up.
- [GRUNTS]

440
00:22:39.930 --> 00:22:42.370
[GROANING]

441
00:22:49.580 --> 00:22:51.780
[PURIFIERS SPEAKING NEARBY]

442
00:22:53.480 --> 00:22:55.880
- [LABORED PANTING]
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

443
00:23:01.090 --> 00:23:02.990
[GROANS]

444
00:23:04.700 --> 00:23:07.120
ERG: John Proudstar.
you look like you need

445
00:23:07.130 --> 00:23:08.459
some help.

446
00:23:08.460 --> 00:23:10.590
How'd you find me?

447
00:23:10.600 --> 00:23:12.829
I know every tunnel
and alley in this city.

448
00:23:12.830 --> 00:23:14.399
I know we've had our disagreements.

449
00:23:14.400 --> 00:23:15.469
I know you hate me.

450
00:23:15.470 --> 00:23:16.599
But.

451
00:23:16.600 --> 00:23:19.500
for Clarice's sake...

452
00:23:19.510 --> 00:23:21.169
I'm hoping you hate them more.

453
00:23:21.170 --> 00:23:24.409
[PANTING]

454
00:23:24.410 --> 00:23:26.340
I don't want your help.

455
00:23:27.610 --> 00:23:28.949
Just let me fight.

456
00:23:28.950 --> 00:23:30.279
You mean let you die?

457
00:23:30.280 --> 00:23:32.749
The Purifiers will be here soon

458
00:23:32.750 --> 00:23:34.149
to finish what they started.

459
00:23:34.150 --> 00:23:37.659
The man who murdered Blink is out there.

460
00:23:37.660 --> 00:23:40.659
You owe it to her not
to let him kill you. too.

461
00:23:40.660 --> 00:23:42.329
[PANTS]

462
00:23:42.330 --> 00:23:45.800
The more energy I absorb.
the more I can send at them.

463
00:23:47.830 --> 00:23:49.030
Hit me.

464
00:23:49.040 --> 00:23:51.470
[PANTING]

465
00:23:52.970 --> 00:23:55.310
[GROANS. GRUNTS]

466
00:23:56.980 --> 00:23:59.709
[PANTING]

467
00:23:59.710 --> 00:24:01.709
[GRUNTS]

468
00:24:01.710 --> 00:24:03.550
- Again.
- [GRUNTING]

469
00:24:05.150 --> 00:24:06.949
Again!

470
00:24:06.950 --> 00:24:09.469
[GRUNTING]

471
00:24:09.470 --> 00:24:11.159
JACE: Am I interrupting something?

472
00:24:11.160 --> 00:24:12.489
You're done.

473
00:24:12.490 --> 00:24:14.690
You're done. Mr. Proudstar.

474
00:24:17.130 --> 00:24:19.539
My name...

475
00:24:19.540 --> 00:24:21.910
is Thunderbird.

476
00:24:27.420 --> 00:24:29.550
[SHOUTS]

477
00:24:31.080 --> 00:24:32.540
[SHOUTS]

478
00:24:32.550 --> 00:24:34.909
[GRUNTING]

479
00:24:34.910 --> 00:24:36.979
- [ARM SNAPS]
- [SCREAMS]

480
00:24:36.980 --> 00:24:39.350
[GRUNTING]

481
00:24:47.530 --> 00:24:50.060
I'm ready to see my little
girl. Just do it. man.

482
00:24:51.260 --> 00:24:53.260
Kill me!

483
00:25:10.570 --> 00:25:12.069
FROST SISTERS: It's time.

484
00:25:12.070 --> 00:25:13.819
You know what you're here for.

485
00:25:13.820 --> 00:25:15.219
Please.

486
00:25:15.220 --> 00:25:16.890
Please don't make us do this.

487
00:25:19.220 --> 00:25:21.120
[SHUDDERS]

488
00:25:21.130 --> 00:25:22.560
[SHOUTING]

489
00:25:25.760 --> 00:25:26.960
Hey. you're hurting her!

490
00:25:26.970 --> 00:25:28.019
PHOEBE/SOPHIE: Then she should

491
00:25:28.020 --> 00:25:29.229
stop resisting.

492
00:25:29.230 --> 00:25:31.369
[LAUREN PANTING]

493
00:25:31.370 --> 00:25:34.670
PHOEBE: Esme. waiting for something?

494
00:25:42.580 --> 00:25:44.750
FROST SISTERS: Time to hold hands.

495
00:25:47.050 --> 00:25:49.149
[GRUNTS]

496
00:25:49.150 --> 00:25:50.550
[PANTING]

497
00:25:54.310 --> 00:25:55.679
Good.

498
00:25:55.680 --> 00:25:58.209
Now. just relax and let go.

499
00:25:58.210 --> 00:25:59.339
[GRUNTS]

500
00:25:59.340 --> 00:26:00.810
♪ ♪

501
00:26:26.410 --> 00:26:28.170
[ANDY AND LAUREN EXHALE]

502
00:26:31.060 --> 00:26:33.980
[SCREAMING IN DISTANCE]

503
00:26:37.720 --> 00:26:38.820
[TIRES SCREECH]

504
00:26:41.720 --> 00:26:44.390
[SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE]

505
00:26:45.860 --> 00:26:48.369
Come any closer and they die.

506
00:26:48.370 --> 00:26:49.739
You shouldn't have come.

507
00:26:49.740 --> 00:26:50.999
You don't have to do this.

508
00:26:51.000 --> 00:26:52.470
Just give them to us and we'll go.

509
00:26:52.480 --> 00:26:54.769
Too late. They're ours now.

510
00:26:54.770 --> 00:26:56.600
- Kill them.
- Kill them all.

511
00:26:57.340 --> 00:26:58.369
No.

512
00:26:58.370 --> 00:26:59.769
- No.
- ANDY: Please! [GRUNTS]

513
00:26:59.770 --> 00:27:01.409
ECLIPSE: Reed. get out of the way.

514
00:27:01.410 --> 00:27:03.339
Marcos. no. they'll kill them!

515
00:27:03.340 --> 00:27:05.570
REED: Andy. Lauren. you have to fight!

516
00:27:05.580 --> 00:27:06.709
Remember who you are.

517
00:27:06.710 --> 00:27:07.780
[GRUNTS]

518
00:27:09.010 --> 00:27:11.540
Esme. Esme. look at me.

519
00:27:12.410 --> 00:27:14.219
[ANDY AND LAUREN PANTING]

520
00:27:14.220 --> 00:27:17.099
You told me that story. about
what the humans did to you

521
00:27:17.100 --> 00:27:19.259
when you were kids. They forced you

522
00:27:19.260 --> 00:27:21.690
to use your powers to
do things that you hated.

523
00:27:22.860 --> 00:27:24.560
How is this any different?

524
00:27:25.820 --> 00:27:27.889
Esme. what is wrong with you?

525
00:27:27.890 --> 00:27:29.039
I...

526
00:27:29.040 --> 00:27:30.120
I can't.

527
00:27:30.130 --> 00:27:31.759
PHOEBE/SOPHIE: There is no "I." Esme.

528
00:27:31.760 --> 00:27:33.909
There's only "we." You're nothing.

529
00:27:33.910 --> 00:27:35.410
No. she's not nothing.

530
00:27:36.270 --> 00:27:37.440
She's my friend.

531
00:27:38.750 --> 00:27:40.449
Marcos. now!

532
00:27:40.450 --> 00:27:41.549
[GRUNTS]

533
00:27:41.550 --> 00:27:42.980
No!

534
00:27:45.450 --> 00:27:48.119
Hey. hey. hey.

535
00:27:48.120 --> 00:27:50.659
- Oh. God.
- [SIREN APPROACHING]

536
00:27:50.660 --> 00:27:52.959
The-the police are close. You
can get away in the tunnels.

537
00:27:52.960 --> 00:27:55.259
- What about you?
- I can't leave them. Just go!

538
00:27:55.260 --> 00:27:57.399
- Go!
- Come on.

539
00:27:57.400 --> 00:27:58.429
I got you.

540
00:27:58.430 --> 00:28:01.069
Oh. my God.

541
00:28:01.070 --> 00:28:03.100
[SIREN WAILING]

542
00:28:07.770 --> 00:28:11.479
POLARIS: Esme told me a little
about how their powers work.

543
00:28:11.480 --> 00:28:12.909
When they force people to do things

544
00:28:12.910 --> 00:28:15.179
that go against
everything they care about.

545
00:28:15.180 --> 00:28:16.679
it. um...

546
00:28:16.680 --> 00:28:18.469
it causes damage.

547
00:28:18.470 --> 00:28:20.079
When they tried to make
me leave the Inner Circle.

548
00:28:20.080 --> 00:28:21.689
dragging me away from our daughter.

549
00:28:21.690 --> 00:28:23.289
it was like my...

550
00:28:23.290 --> 00:28:25.089
brain was in a vice.

551
00:28:25.090 --> 00:28:27.590
I think they're lucky to be alive.

552
00:28:28.930 --> 00:28:31.099
[WEAKLY]: Mom. Dad. I'm...

553
00:28:31.100 --> 00:28:32.329
I'm so sorry.

554
00:28:32.330 --> 00:28:34.799
What are you sorry for?

555
00:28:34.800 --> 00:28:35.970
The building.

556
00:28:36.630 --> 00:28:37.769
We destroyed it.

557
00:28:37.770 --> 00:28:39.020
All those people.

558
00:28:39.030 --> 00:28:41.089
No. that-that was not your fault.

559
00:28:41.090 --> 00:28:43.249
You didn't do anything.

560
00:28:43.250 --> 00:28:46.049
You didn't have control of your powers.

561
00:28:46.050 --> 00:28:47.379
We could've killed you.

562
00:28:47.380 --> 00:28:49.349
You saved us.

563
00:28:49.350 --> 00:28:52.170
We have the chance to
stop what's about to happen

564
00:28:52.180 --> 00:28:53.349
because of you.

565
00:28:53.350 --> 00:28:56.359
REED: I saw how hard you fought.

566
00:28:56.360 --> 00:28:58.530
I've never been prouder of you both.

567
00:28:59.890 --> 00:29:01.449
We need to move.

568
00:29:01.450 --> 00:29:03.199
They are in no shape to fight.

569
00:29:03.200 --> 00:29:04.699
- They can barely even walk.
- Okay. well.

570
00:29:04.700 --> 00:29:06.299
we can drop them off at the scrapyard.

571
00:29:06.300 --> 00:29:07.999
We can't just leave them there.

572
00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:09.239
Cait. I hate it. too.

573
00:29:09.240 --> 00:29:11.219
But they will never be safe

574
00:29:11.220 --> 00:29:12.690
while Reeva is out there.

575
00:29:12.700 --> 00:29:15.810
If we don't stop her now. we
might never get the chance.

576
00:29:17.350 --> 00:29:19.210
♪ ♪

577
00:29:30.530 --> 00:29:31.820
That's the building.

578
00:29:33.830 --> 00:29:35.390
It's big.

579
00:29:35.400 --> 00:29:37.379
POLARIS: Yeah. Top floors
are the Inner Circle.

580
00:29:37.380 --> 00:29:38.829
How do we get up there?

581
00:29:38.830 --> 00:29:41.030
There's a private parking
garage with a freight elevator.

582
00:29:41.040 --> 00:29:42.959
What about guards and security?

583
00:29:42.960 --> 00:29:44.190
Security's on the outside.

584
00:29:44.200 --> 00:29:45.959
I can get us in. Once we're up there.

585
00:29:45.960 --> 00:29:48.319
most of Reeva's people will
be out with the strike team.

586
00:29:48.320 --> 00:29:50.879
Well. even by herself.
Reeva's bad enough.

587
00:29:50.880 --> 00:29:53.059
Look. when she attacks us.
we won't be able to think.

588
00:29:53.060 --> 00:29:54.749
We won't be able to control our powers.

589
00:29:54.750 --> 00:29:56.780
Just tell me this.

590
00:29:59.220 --> 00:30:01.550
If we stop Reeva. this ends?

591
00:30:01.560 --> 00:30:03.630
Without her. the whole
thing falls apart.

592
00:30:08.560 --> 00:30:10.960
♪ ♪

593
00:30:23.380 --> 00:30:24.579
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.

594
00:30:24.580 --> 00:30:25.949
Is that safe? Those go off...

595
00:30:25.950 --> 00:30:27.099
I know what I'm doing.

596
00:30:27.100 --> 00:30:28.949
Still like the old-fashioned way.

597
00:30:28.950 --> 00:30:30.509
You know. the team shouldn't have to use

598
00:30:30.510 --> 00:30:31.549
these explosives at all.

599
00:30:31.550 --> 00:30:32.889
If Max was here. we wouldn't need

600
00:30:32.890 --> 00:30:33.970
any of this crap.

601
00:30:34.720 --> 00:30:36.719
Hey. if it gets the job done.

602
00:30:36.720 --> 00:30:37.920
works for me.

603
00:30:37.930 --> 00:30:39.089
[CLATTERING NEARBY]

604
00:30:39.090 --> 00:30:40.590
What the hell?

605
00:30:47.670 --> 00:30:49.639
ECLIPSE: Okay. so. where is

606
00:30:49.640 --> 00:30:51.600
- this elevator. huh?
- At the other end.

607
00:30:53.640 --> 00:30:54.970
Take cover!

608
00:31:02.480 --> 00:31:03.720
[GRUNTING]

609
00:31:06.360 --> 00:31:07.710
[SHOUTS]

610
00:31:12.440 --> 00:31:14.500
[PANTING]

611
00:31:16.130 --> 00:31:17.630
[GRUNTING]

612
00:31:22.090 --> 00:31:23.310
Ah!

613
00:31:25.370 --> 00:31:27.250
Let's get to the elevator. Come on.

614
00:31:29.210 --> 00:31:30.710
Come on.

615
00:31:31.710 --> 00:31:33.110
Wait.

616
00:31:36.120 --> 00:31:37.450
[GRUNTING]

617
00:31:40.770 --> 00:31:42.369
[PANTS] All right. Let's go.

618
00:31:42.370 --> 00:31:45.120
[GRUNTING]

619
00:31:45.130 --> 00:31:46.789
Reed.

620
00:31:46.790 --> 00:31:48.830
[GUNSHOTS]

621
00:31:52.070 --> 00:31:53.570
[GRUNTS]

622
00:31:56.120 --> 00:31:57.430
[GROANING]

623
00:32:00.640 --> 00:32:02.200
Nice shot.

624
00:32:04.680 --> 00:32:06.149
Ah.

625
00:32:06.150 --> 00:32:08.770
[GASPS] It looks like
they've got their hands full.

626
00:32:08.780 --> 00:32:10.760
We're not gonna have time
to wait for them. I should

627
00:32:10.770 --> 00:32:12.719
go up alone. You cover me.
and I'll get to the elevator.

628
00:32:12.720 --> 00:32:14.859
What are you talking about?
We've got a slim enough chance

629
00:32:14.860 --> 00:32:16.319
- with the four of us.
- Listen to me.

630
00:32:16.320 --> 00:32:17.429
- [EXPLOSION]
- [GASPS]

631
00:32:17.430 --> 00:32:19.609
Reeva makes people lose
control of their powers.

632
00:32:19.610 --> 00:32:21.390
And I already can't control mine.

633
00:32:21.400 --> 00:32:22.899
We can use that. We have to.

634
00:32:22.900 --> 00:32:24.450
- [EXPLOSION]
- [GASPS]

635
00:32:24.460 --> 00:32:26.720
- What are you saying?
- Since I stopped my medicine.

636
00:32:26.730 --> 00:32:30.669
the episodes have become
more severe. more frequent.

637
00:32:30.670 --> 00:32:33.439
We know from Dr. Risman
that the energy eventually

638
00:32:33.440 --> 00:32:36.430
is gonna tear me apart. I can
barely control it right now.

639
00:32:36.440 --> 00:32:37.709
- Reed.
- If she were

640
00:32:37.710 --> 00:32:39.579
to attack me and that
power were to be released?

641
00:32:39.580 --> 00:32:42.410
- It would kill you.
- And everyone who's up there with me.

642
00:32:42.420 --> 00:32:45.419
- But it might stop her.
- [EXPLOSIONS]

643
00:32:45.420 --> 00:32:47.770
Listen. you always said to me
that things happen

644
00:32:47.780 --> 00:32:49.719
- for a reason. and you were right.
- No.

645
00:32:49.720 --> 00:32:52.289
Take care of our family.
Take care of our kids.

646
00:32:52.290 --> 00:32:54.150
No. No. no. no. You can't
do this. you can't...

647
00:32:54.160 --> 00:32:55.690
I have to. It's the only way.

648
00:33:00.300 --> 00:33:02.569
I love you.

649
00:33:02.570 --> 00:33:04.539
Reed!

650
00:33:04.540 --> 00:33:05.600
Over there!

651
00:33:07.040 --> 00:33:08.770
[GASPING]

652
00:33:18.150 --> 00:33:19.950
[GASPS]

653
00:33:21.490 --> 00:33:23.620
I love you.

654
00:33:25.660 --> 00:33:29.300
[PANTING]

655
00:33:36.240 --> 00:33:39.069
CAITLIN: Did you believe that?

656
00:33:39.070 --> 00:33:41.270
What you said to Lauren earlier

657
00:33:41.280 --> 00:33:43.809
about things happening for a reason?

658
00:33:43.810 --> 00:33:46.179
- You were listening?
- Maybe.

659
00:33:46.180 --> 00:33:48.110
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

660
00:33:48.120 --> 00:33:49.749
[SIGHS] I don't know.

661
00:33:49.750 --> 00:33:51.980
I was just trying to let
her see that something good

662
00:33:51.990 --> 00:33:55.119
- can come of this.
- Hmm.

663
00:33:55.120 --> 00:33:58.620
I-I think it's deeper than that.

664
00:33:58.630 --> 00:34:00.790
I think that our

665
00:34:00.800 --> 00:34:05.830
challenges and our tragedies
are ours for a reason.

666
00:34:07.770 --> 00:34:10.339
Maybe that's true.

667
00:34:10.340 --> 00:34:14.939
I do sometimes think that
I've got a role to play

668
00:34:14.940 --> 00:34:17.879
in all of this. in the mutant situation.

669
00:34:17.880 --> 00:34:19.810
in keeping us all safe.

670
00:34:21.820 --> 00:34:24.319
I wish I knew what it was.

671
00:34:24.320 --> 00:34:26.690
[RAPID PANTING]

672
00:34:33.830 --> 00:34:36.500
[ELEVATOR BELL CHIMES]

673
00:34:53.630 --> 00:34:57.360
RYAN: Hundreds of American heroes
died today in a cowardly attack

674
00:34:57.370 --> 00:35:01.169
on Sentinel Services
by mutant terrorists.

675
00:35:01.170 --> 00:35:03.620
We must honor their sacrifice.

676
00:35:03.630 --> 00:35:05.259
Defend the America they loved

677
00:35:05.260 --> 00:35:07.779
and swore an allegiance to protect.

678
00:35:07.780 --> 00:35:11.080
It is time to define what
makes someone an American.

679
00:35:11.180 --> 00:35:13.819
- REED: Reeva. it's over.
- RYAN: Reevaluate the criteria...

680
00:35:13.820 --> 00:35:16.180
- [TV MUTES]
- So...

681
00:35:16.260 --> 00:35:19.690
the most disappointing
of the von Struckers.

682
00:35:19.700 --> 00:35:22.329
What a surprise. I... I thought

683
00:35:22.330 --> 00:35:24.690
they'd send someone more formidable.

684
00:35:27.970 --> 00:35:29.969
I've been keeping tabs on you

685
00:35:29.970 --> 00:35:31.599
over the years. you know.

686
00:35:31.600 --> 00:35:33.399
Fighting against mutants.

687
00:35:33.400 --> 00:35:36.340
fighting for them. fighting
your own mutant powers.

688
00:35:37.700 --> 00:35:41.009
You're so... confused.

689
00:35:41.010 --> 00:35:42.940
Maybe once.

690
00:35:42.950 --> 00:35:45.049
Not anymore.

691
00:35:45.050 --> 00:35:46.749
You need to stop this.

692
00:35:46.750 --> 00:35:48.850
Why would I stop now? We've only

693
00:35:48.860 --> 00:35:50.949
just begun. and I'm
not sure if you've been

694
00:35:50.950 --> 00:35:53.089
paying attention. but this revolution

695
00:35:53.090 --> 00:35:55.420
of ours is moving forward
one way or another.

696
00:35:56.290 --> 00:35:58.329
Humans and mutants couldn't
live together before.

697
00:35:58.330 --> 00:36:01.289
Because you and the Purifiers
have made sure that they can't.

698
00:36:01.290 --> 00:36:04.730
Oh. please. I only helped
along the inevitable.

699
00:36:04.740 --> 00:36:07.019
You know. your grandparents understood

700
00:36:07.020 --> 00:36:08.469
what it takes to create a homeland.

701
00:36:08.470 --> 00:36:11.339
It's such a shame that you never could.

702
00:36:11.340 --> 00:36:14.709
You can't build a nation on
the murder of innocent people.

703
00:36:14.710 --> 00:36:16.339
Read your history books.

704
00:36:16.340 --> 00:36:19.090
That is the <i>only</i> way
that you can build a nation.

705
00:36:19.100 --> 00:36:21.319
It's too bad. really.

706
00:36:21.320 --> 00:36:23.950
Your family name could
have lived on forever.

707
00:36:29.860 --> 00:36:32.460
[SINGING HIGH TONE]

708
00:37:01.660 --> 00:37:04.260
♪ ♪

709
00:37:34.260 --> 00:37:36.960
♪ ♪

710
00:37:41.530 --> 00:37:43.760
[SINGING HIGH TONE]

711
00:37:48.370 --> 00:37:50.400
[GRUNTING]

712
00:37:51.810 --> 00:37:54.420
You wanted the power
of the von Struckers?

713
00:37:57.910 --> 00:38:00.750
It's all yours.

714
00:38:04.150 --> 00:38:06.890
[GASPS]

715
00:38:07.890 --> 00:38:09.120
[SHOUTS]

716
00:38:15.830 --> 00:38:17.370
Let's go!

717
00:38:40.210 --> 00:38:42.349
LAUREN: <i>We weren't there
when we lost you.</i>

718
00:38:42.350 --> 00:38:45.460
<i>And we'll live with that
for the rest of our lives.</i>

719
00:38:52.440 --> 00:38:54.839
ANDY: <i>But we know that what you did.</i>

720
00:38:54.840 --> 00:38:57.200
<i>you did for all of us.</i>

721
00:38:58.620 --> 00:39:03.430
♪ There is a house
built out of stone... ♪

722
00:39:06.350 --> 00:39:09.219
LAUREN: <i>You died so we
could come together.</i>

723
00:39:09.220 --> 00:39:12.389
♪ And windowsills... ♪

724
00:39:12.390 --> 00:39:15.119
<i>So we could heal.</i>

725
00:39:15.120 --> 00:39:21.859
♪ Tables and chairs
worn by all of the dust ♪

726
00:39:21.860 --> 00:39:24.729
ANDY: <i>You died to stop hate.</i>

727
00:39:24.730 --> 00:39:30.500
♪ This is a place where
I don't feel alone... ♪

728
00:39:30.510 --> 00:39:32.409
LAUREN: <i>And you died</i>

729
00:39:32.410 --> 00:39:35.009
<i>so we could be with the people we love.</i>

730
00:39:35.010 --> 00:39:38.579
<i>Te amo.</i> Aurorita. <i>Estamos aquí.</i>

731
00:39:38.580 --> 00:39:41.110
We'll all be together soon. baby girl.

732
00:39:41.120 --> 00:39:43.220
For good.

733
00:39:48.030 --> 00:39:50.129
ANDY: <i>We're still fighting.</i>

734
00:39:50.130 --> 00:39:53.330
Mr. Ryan. any comment on reports
you were involved in the attack?

735
00:39:53.340 --> 00:39:54.990
I have nothing to say.

736
00:39:55.000 --> 00:39:56.399
LAUREN: <i>We're fighting in ways</i>

737
00:39:56.400 --> 00:39:58.769
<i>that were never possible before.</i>

738
00:39:58.770 --> 00:40:03.769
RYAN/ESME: Actually. I
do have something to say.

739
00:40:03.770 --> 00:40:06.209
It's time I confess my crimes.

740
00:40:06.210 --> 00:40:07.609
REPORTER: Mr. Ryan. Mr. Ryan!

741
00:40:07.610 --> 00:40:09.179
What exactly do you mean?

742
00:40:09.180 --> 00:40:10.810
I've been secretly leading

743
00:40:10.820 --> 00:40:13.650
the Purifiers for over f-five years.

744
00:40:15.360 --> 00:40:18.080
♪ Until ♪

745
00:40:18.090 --> 00:40:23.459
♪ It disappeared ♪

746
00:40:23.460 --> 00:40:25.359
♪ From me... ♪

747
00:40:25.360 --> 00:40:28.280
LAUREN: <i>We will keep fighting.
but I want you to know.</i>

748
00:40:30.190 --> 00:40:31.649
I love you. Daddy.

749
00:40:31.650 --> 00:40:33.329
♪ And now... ♪

750
00:40:33.330 --> 00:40:34.699
I love you. Dad.

751
00:40:34.700 --> 00:40:37.200
♪ It's time... ♪

752
00:40:37.210 --> 00:40:39.209
Goodbye. Reed.

753
00:40:39.210 --> 00:40:42.779
♪ Leave ♪

754
00:40:42.780 --> 00:40:47.210
♪ And turn ♪

755
00:40:47.220 --> 00:40:51.490
♪ To dust. ♪

756
00:40:54.990 --> 00:40:58.229
ERG: <i>I know it's a hard time to meet.</i>

757
00:40:58.230 --> 00:41:00.090
But a situation has arisen.

758
00:41:00.100 --> 00:41:02.660
The Morlocks in DC are gone.

759
00:41:02.670 --> 00:41:04.780
but in the past couple
weeks I've had contact

760
00:41:04.800 --> 00:41:06.569
with some people in other cities.

761
00:41:06.570 --> 00:41:07.999
I hear things.

762
00:41:08.000 --> 00:41:09.769
Reeva Payge may be gone.

763
00:41:09.770 --> 00:41:12.439
but the Mutant Uprising
she sparked is not.

764
00:41:12.440 --> 00:41:13.839
And what does that mean?

765
00:41:13.840 --> 00:41:16.179
That mutant groups are gathering.

766
00:41:16.180 --> 00:41:18.749
Some in the wilderness. some in cities.

767
00:41:18.750 --> 00:41:20.749
What does that have to do with us?

768
00:41:20.750 --> 00:41:23.150
ERG: People have heard of this group.

769
00:41:24.150 --> 00:41:25.750
What happened with the Purifiers.

770
00:41:25.760 --> 00:41:27.759
Your family's sacrifice.

771
00:41:27.760 --> 00:41:30.020
They need help.

772
00:41:30.030 --> 00:41:31.329
Leadership.

773
00:41:31.330 --> 00:41:33.659
ECLIPSE: Well. do they understand

774
00:41:33.660 --> 00:41:35.430
the Mutant Underground is gone?

775
00:41:37.300 --> 00:41:38.720
CAITLIN: It's all right. Marcos.

776
00:41:38.730 --> 00:41:40.769
We'll make a new one.

777
00:41:40.770 --> 00:41:42.700
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY] Good.

778
00:41:44.640 --> 00:41:47.870
There are some camps
not too far from here.

779
00:41:47.880 --> 00:41:49.640
John. what is it?

780
00:41:50.870 --> 00:41:52.310
Something's. uh...

